===Alternative forms===
* [[dogmatical]]

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|dogmatique}}, from {{etyl|LL.|en}} {{m|la|dogmaticus}}, from Hellenistic {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|δογματικός||didactic}}, from {{m|grc|δόγμα||dogma}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/dɒɡˈmatɪk/|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# {{label|en|philosophy|medicine}} Adhering only to [[principle]]s which are true ''[[a priori]]'', rather than truths based on evidence or deduction.
# Pertaining to [[dogma]]s; [[doctrinal]].
# Asserting [[dogma]]s or [[belief]]s in a superior or arrogant way; [[opinionated]], [[dictatorial]].

